00:02:56.670 --> 00:02:58.400
We could think of
it intuitively.

00:02:58.400 --> 00:03:02.010
How fast am I decelerating?

00:03:02.010 --> 00:03:07.470
So I'm decelerating at the
rate of gravity, right?

00:03:07.470 --> 00:03:09.510
And we know that cause that's
what's slowing down the ball.

00:03:09.510 --> 00:03:13.450
So we know that acceleration
is equal to minus 10 meters

00:03:13.450 --> 00:03:15.700
per second squared.

00:03:15.700 --> 00:03:16.900
And so what do we do?

00:03:16.900 --> 00:03:19.735
Well acceleration is the same
thing as a change in velocity.

00:03:23.460 --> 00:03:25.385
Acceleration times time
is the same thing as

00:03:25.385 --> 00:03:26.590
the change in velocity.

00:03:26.590 --> 00:03:29.010
Or the change in velocity
divided by time is

00:03:29.010 --> 00:03:30.610
acceleration.

00:03:30.610 --> 00:03:31.150
So let's say that.

00:03:31.150 --> 00:03:31.875
It's a change in velocity.

00:03:31.875 --> 00:03:38.510
Well the change in velocity is
equal to the final velocity

00:03:38.510 --> 00:03:40.580
minus the initial velocity.

00:03:40.580 --> 00:03:42.710
And that equals acceleration
times time.

00:03:42.710 --> 00:03:50.040
So minus 10 meters per second
squared-- I'll stick with the

00:03:50.040 --> 00:03:51.480
units this time-- times time.

00:03:51.480 --> 00:03:56.710
So it did that in 3-1/2 seconds,
times 3.5 seconds.

00:03:56.710 --> 00:03:59.600
So this seconds cancels out with
one of the seconds in the

00:03:59.600 --> 00:04:01.970
denominator here.

00:04:01.970 --> 00:04:13.020
